post_text: MHS kicked off their golf season last week by hosting three meets at Shewami Country Club. Tuesday, Milford won with a score of 194 for the boys and 238 for the girls. Meet medalist was CJ VanHoveln with a 43. For the girls, Anna Hagan was second place with a 54 and Kristin Butler was third with a 60. Wednesday, both boys and girls won 1 and lost 2. The boys had a low team score of 195 and girls had a low team score of 238. Thursday, Milford came in 3rd with the boys scoring 185 and the girls scoring 241. The boys' record is now 4-4 and the girls' record is 2-4. The next meet for both boys and girls is on 8/25 at Harrison Park, beginning at 4:15. #MHSBearcatNation

post_text:
2020-2021 Preschool
In order to allow our teachers and youngest students some time to acclimate to the ISBE guidelines, MGS will move forward with small preschool classes. We will invite students who were enrolled in class last school year, first. After the class has some experience with how to implement procedures for our youngest students, we will then invite those 4 year olds who had previously signed up for screenings to be screened and enrolled. If space allows, we will then open up screening to additional 4 year olds and then 3 year olds. We understand that this is different than in the past, but we want to 1) ensure we know how to best serve our littles and keep them safe and 2) ensure that our 4 year olds who will enter kindergarten next year are served. We will send a message when we will start the screening process and those that had been signed up will be contacted. We appreciate your understanding through the unknown. ğŸ’šğŸ¦‡ğŸ”¥ ##mbats202021 #leadteachlearnwithpassion
text:
2020-2021 Preschool
In order to allow our teachers and youngest students some time to acclimate to the ISBE guidelines, MGS will move forward with small preschool classes. We will invite students who were enrolled in class last school year, first. After the class has some experience with how to implement procedures for our youngest students, we will then invite those 4 year olds who had previously signed up for screenings to be screened and enrolled. If space allows, we will then open up screening to additional 4 year olds and then 3 year olds. We understand that this is different than in the past, but we want to 1) ensure we know how to best serve our littles and keep them safe and 2) ensure that our 4 year olds who will enter kindergarten next year are served. We will send a message when we will start the screening process and those that had been signed up will be contacted. We appreciate your understanding through the unknown. ğŸ’šğŸ¦‡ğŸ”¥ ##mbats202021 #leadteachlearnwithpassion

post_text:
MGS Rocks & Continues to Grow!!

Join Us in this School Wide Activity to Build a Rock Garden

WHO: ALL OF YOU--Students, Parents, Teachers, Families and Friends

WHAT: A MGS Rock Garden

WHERE: At the Front Entrance of Milford Grade School

WHEN: NOW

WHY: Because MGS will continue to grow and work together.

Please spend time with your families painting small rocks (1in-5in rocks) with positive messages, inspiring words, and fun pictures. You can grab some unpainted rocks from our garden if you need rocks to paint. When you are finished painting your rocks, come back to MGS and add them to the garden. Drive thru the bus lane to drop your painted rocks off in the garden. You will see the garden as you near the front doors of the grade school entrance.

Please adhere to the following schedule:

Seniors: Monday, May 18th, 2020 from 8:00 - 11:00 am.

All students Freshmen thru Juniors may drop off/pickup on any of the following days/time:
Tuesday, May 26th, 2020 from 8:00 - 11:00 AM and 3:00 - 6:00 PM
Wednesday, May 27th, 2020 from 8:00 - 11:00 AM and 3:00 - 6:00 PM
Thursday, May 28th, 2020 from 8:00 - 11:00 AM and 3:00 - 6:00 PM

Please enter the south student parking lot following the arrows and school personnel will direct you to a dropoff location. Please follow the directions of school personnel and do not exit your vehicle at any time. Staff members wearing appropriate PPE will visit your vehicle, collect student materials, and return student items that may remain in lockers and classrooms. If you have multiple high school students, please assist in having each student's materials separated to assist in the return process.
